+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019YD9WfP6Yj6yhcpseFmuN5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Structure Analysis - /workspace\n\n### **Overview**\nThis is a **Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor Server** project called \"bench-collab-server\" (v1.0.0). It's a TypeScript-based Node.js project using Express and WebSockets.\n\n---\n\n### **1. ROOT-LEVEL FILES**\n\n#### **package.json** - `/workspace/package.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-collab-server\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Real-time collaborative editing benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"ws\": \"^8.18.0\",\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/ws\": \"^8.5.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Scripts Available:**\n- `npm run build` - Compiles TypeScript to JavaScript\n- `npm run lint` - Runs ESLint on src/ directory\n- `npm run test` - Runs Vitest test suite\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- **ws** (^8.18.0) - WebSocket library\n- **better-sqlite3** (^11.0.0) - SQLite database\n- **express** (^4.21.0) - HTTP web framework\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- TypeScript (^5.4.0) with full type definitions\n- Testing: vitest (^2.0.0), supertest (^7.0.0), coverage\n- Linting: ESLint (^8.56.0) with TypeScript support\n\n---\n\n#### **tsconfig.json** - `/wo