BLE IF NOT EXISTS documents (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  title TEXT NOT NULL,\n  content TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS versions (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  document_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES documents(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  version INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  content TEXT NOT NULL,\n  operation TEXT, -- JSON of the operation that produced this version\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  UNIQUE(document_id, version)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS active_connections (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  document_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES documents(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  connected_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n);\n```\n\n**Database Schema:**\n- **documents** - Stores document title and content with timestamps\n- **versions** - Tracks version history with operations for conflict resolution\n- **active_connections** - Tracks concurrent WebSocket connections per document\n\n---\n\n#### **.gitignore** - `/workspace/.gitignore`\n```\nnode_modules/\ndist/\n*.db\n*.sqlite\n```\n\nIgnores node dependencies, compiled output, and SQLite databases.\n\n---\n\n#### **TASK.md** - `/workspace/TASK.md`\nProject requirements document. Key points:\n- Build a real-time collaborative document editor (like Google Docs)\n- REST API for CRUD operations with version history\n- WebSocket for real-time collaboration\n- Conflict resolution using Operational Transform (OT) or CRDTs\n- SQLite persistence\n- Handle 10+ concurrent clients\n- Entry point: `createApp()` factory function from `src/server.ts` or `src/index.ts`\n\n---\n\n#### **.thunderdome/rubric.yaml** - `/workspace/.thunderdome/rubric.yaml`\nScoring rubric with 100 total points across:\n- Build (10 pts)\n- Lint (5 pts)\n- REST CRUD (15 pts, 10 tests)\n- WebSocket Lifecycle (15 pts, 8 tests)\n- Single Client Editing (10 pts, 6 tests)\n- Two-Client C